      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed on the pedicle screw shank and rod junction region. Stiffness QoI changes 1.4% between medium (1.2M elements) and fine (3.1M elements) mesh. GCI = 3.2%. Production mesh uses medium density. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative solver tolerance set to 1e-6; Newton-Raphson convergence monitored each substep; no unconverged substeps in production runs.",
      "rationale": "Sparse direct solver (SPARSE) used for linear substeps; full Newton-Raphson with line search for nonlinear contact iterations. All 11 construct simulations converge within 25 equilibrium iterations per load step. No solver warnings or unconverged substeps recorded. Gradation 2 satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent analyst review of boundary conditions, material assignments, and contact definitions; checklist-based QC sign-off prior to each simulation run.",
      "rationale": "Each modeling team completed a structured pre-run checklist covering boundary condition assignment, material property mapping, contact pair definition, and load application direction. Cross-team review of input decks performed before final production runs. No use errors identified during review. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Bilinear isotropic hardening plasticity with kinematic hardening used for Ti-6Al-4V; contact modeled with augmented Lagrangian formulation; geometric nonlinearity enabled.",
      "rationale": "Model form selection justified by prior literature on metallic implant FEA. Bilinear kinematic hardening parameters calibrated to ASTM E8 tensile coupon data for the specific Ti-6Al-4V alloy lot. Frictional contact (mu=0.2) applied at screw-rod and rod-block interfaces. Large-deformation formulation active throughout. Model form uncertainty quantified via sensitivity analysis showing <3% QoI sensitivity to friction coefficient over range 0.15–0.30. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from lot-specific tensile testing; geometry from calibrated CMM measurements of production components; input uncertainty propagated via one-at-a-time sensitivity study.",
      "rationale": "Young's modulus (113.8 GPa), yield strength (880 MPa), and tangent modulus (2.1 GPa) obtained from lot-specific ASTM E8 testing (n=5 coupons). Screw and rod geometry digitized via CMM to within ±0.01 mm. Sensitivity analysis confirms stiffness QoI dominated by rod diameter (±0.05 mm → ±1.9% stiffness). All input distributions documented. Gradation 2 satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N=11 constructs from production lot; dimensional inspection confirms within-specification geometry; traceability to device history records maintained.",
      "rationale": "Eleven non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs assembled from production-representative components. CMM inspection of each screw and rod confirms geometry within drawing tolerances. Lot traceability and device history records archived. Sample size sufficient for statistical comparison per ASTM F1717. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of clinically relevant loading scenarios including at least two distinct loading rates or construct configurations.",
      "rationale": "Experimental testing performed exclusively under ASTM F1717 standard quasi-static compression-bending at a single crosshead displacement rate (5 mm/min) and a single construct configuration (L4-L5 two-level). No variation in loading rate, angular offset, or block spacing was explored. While the single condition is protocol-compliant, it does not satisfy the Gradation 2 requirement for test condition breadth applicable to this model risk level. Achieved level remains Gradation 1. This shortfall was identified during factor assessment and noted in the decision record; however, the overall package was judged acceptable given strong inter-laboratory reproducibility and ensemble agreement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA boundary conditions demonstrably equivalent to experimental fixture constraints; block compliance characterized and incorporated into model.",
      "rationale": "UHMWPE block compliance measured via instrumented compression test and incorporated as elastic foundation boundary condition in FEA. Fixture grip compliance characterized and subtracted from experimental displacement measurements. Equivalency of applied displacement rate confirmed by comparing FEA quasi-static assumption against experimental strain-rate data (peak strain rate 0.002/s, well within quasi-static regime). Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric E/uval < 1.96 and percent difference < 10% for all primary QoIs; uncertainty in both model predictions and experimental measurements propagated.",
      "rationale": "Validation metric E/uval computed per ASME V&V 40 Section 5 incorporating experimental measurement uncertainty (inter-lab COV 3.2%) and model prediction uncertainty (mesh, material, geometry). Results: stiffness E/uval = 1.31, yield force E/uval = 1.18, force at 40 mm E/uval = 0.94. All three QoIs satisfy E/uval < 1.96 and percent difference < 10%. Gradation 2 achieved across all three modeling teams independently."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) directly linked to clinical failure modes and regulatory submission requirements.",
      "rationale": "The three QoIs are the primary outputs specified in ASTM F1717 and directly correspond to construct stiffness (functional performance), yield force (onset of permanent deformation), and ultimate load-bearing capacity (safety margin). These QoIs are the same quantities used in the regulatory substantial equivalence comparison. Direct clinical relevance to fatigue initiation and revision surgery risk established in literature. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
